4 stars because as far as gratins go, this one's a keeper! I tried this recipe for Christmas and got excellent feedback from my guests! A few notes: The recipe serves 10; I made the recipe twice (for 14 as part of a buffet), and there was almost an entire gratin left over that everyone wanted to take home. I used a total of 5 pounds fresh spinach but frozen would work just as well in this case. The butternut squash was very tough to peel/slice. I made slices using a de Buyer mandoline and found it more attractive to cut the squash into rectangular blocks before slicing, which made arranging the slices easy and neat. Also, I prepared the gratins covered in parchment and then tin foil 1 day in advance and let them return to room temp before cooking. The parmesan seems to be missing from the recipe, but I sprinkled the top layer generously to create a bubbling crust. I recommend and will make again.

