Rating: 4
I have now made this dish many times for dinner parties. Each time it receives lavish praise. Use fresh loose baby spinach leaves for the best taste. It seems like you're buying a lot of spinach but it boils down to a very small volume. It pays to really squeeze out the spinach or else the dish comes out watery. The one drawback of this dish is that it is a bit time consuming. Peeling butternut squash is a chore, and even with a cuisinart, the dish does take a while to prepare. I only make it for special occasions and I make it ahead in the morning. It takes much longer to cook than the recipie says - allot about an hour or more. You don't want the squash to come out tough.

