Rating: 4
Made this thanksgiving with Ted Allen's Thanksgiving menu. The gratin was delicious. I too added parm in between layers based on reviews. Are you kidding about using a mandoline??? I started this way and quickly switched over to the food processor. Food processor on smallest slice mode was immensely faster, easier, and produced more uniform slices. I also used frozen spinach in the bag (not the block of spinach) which needed very little squeezing to remove water. I'd recommend this if you have bags instead of boxes of frozen spinach available. When making the layers, I'd recommend very light layers, mostly of 'globs' of spinach with space between them. It's the squash on squash action in between layers which allows the gratin to set and not slide all over the place because of a large spinach layer. I prepared the day before, let sit at room temp about an hour before cooking. I also used a convection oven, so cooking time was less, not more, than recommended. I loved it, but if you have some folks who just don't like sweet dishes, you might want to have some mashed potatoes on hand just in case. Will DEFINITELY make this again.

