I "weight watcher-ized" this recipe (and changed it a bit), with fantastic results. The same unique, delicious taste with a fraction of the calories and fat. (Note: I also halved this recipe, so the quantities are for ½ the recipe). First, I sautéed the onions and garlic in Pam. Second, I cubed the butternut squash and par boiled in vegetable broth. I then steamed the spinach in vegetable broth. Then for the creamed spinach, I used all the recommended seasonings (plus a dash of splenda, I like sweet vegetables). I then substituted ¼ cup fat free half and half for the heavy cream, and added 1 tablespoon parmesan and mixed well. I then stirred in the butternut squash and placed the entire mixture into a casserole dish and sprinkled with 1 tablespoon grated parm and cooked as directed. Delicious, and I dont miss the butter or heavy cream or fat.

