I made this with a couple of variations. I'm not so into heavy cream so instead made a classic bechamel (4 tbs butter + 3 tbs flour in a heavy bottom sauce pan; add 2 cups 1% milk gradually while wisking, salt, white pepper, pinch of nutmet) and stirred the onion/spinach mixture into the bechamel. i then layered the butternut squash slices (pre-roasted for 20 min. in a 450 oven to bring out the sweetness) with the bechamel to make a "lasagna" type structure. it was delicious!

