Rating: 3
The adjustable blade slicer is not a common item. I tried to slice with a knife and found it difficult.A food processor did not give elongated slices. However, microwaving the peeled squash 3-4 minutes at high power and checking the texture each time made the slicing much easier.Not soft, but just pliable to slice with a good knife.

Rating: 3
I assembled the dish the night before to bring to my friend's house for dinner. They are both vegetarians so I thought this dish was perfect. Since I have a cheap imitation of a mandolin, I had to 8th my butternut squash (instead of quarter). The next day, I only let it sit at room temperature for 30 minutes and ended up increasing my cooking time by 10 minutes. This dish looks exactly like the picture when cooked. The delicate flavor of the squash is not overwhelmed by the spinach but it is not as creamy as you might expect in an au gratin. We paired this dish with a salad for a meal but I could see this as part of a large feast. If you know anyone who thinks squash is bitter if not cooked as a dessert, this is an excellent example of how this vegetable can shine. Overall, an excellent dish.